Adidas, Beiersdorf, ProSieben, Repower: German Equity Preview

-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 
2011-05-05T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/adidas-beiersdorf-prosieben-repower-german-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  Germany . Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  The benchmark DAX Index fell 126.77 points, or 1.7 percent,
to 7,373.93.  Adidas AG (ADS)  : The world’s second-largest sporting
goods maker, striving to improve after a fourth-quarter profit
decline, will report its first-quarter earnings. Shares of the
company fell 0.7 percent to 49.89 euros.  Beiersdorf AG (BEI)  : The German maker of Nivea skin
cream is reporting first-quarter results. Last month, Hamburg-
based Beiersdorf reiterated a 2011 forecast of unchanged revenue
and lower margins for its consumer-products division. The
company’s shares rose 0.5 percent to 43.93 euros.  ProSiebenSat.1 AG (PSM GY): Germany’s biggest private
broadcaster, which is trying to cut debt, will present first-
quarter results after agreeing to sell its Dutch and Belgian
operations in April. The shares of the company fell 2.2 percent
to 18.32 euros.  Repower Systems AG (RPW)  : Shares of the German maker of
offshore  wind turbines  may gain after newspapers reported that
Chancellor  Angela Merkel  may increase tariffs payable on power
generated by the renewable energy source. Shares of Hamburg-
based Repower fell 2.4 percent to 140.65 euros.  E.ON AG (EOAN)  : The Essen-based utility company holds
its annual general meeting amid calls by Chief Executive Officer
Johannes Teyssen for the government not to slash the operational
life-cycle of its nuclear plants after the Fukushima disaster in
 Japan . The shares of E.ON fell 1.9 percent to 22.81 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Parkin in Berlin at 
 bparkin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  